b9cc21bd2657f8539beec59caca3e0b97affedf78f3994c910d686208169bbab,day1866,sea_level_indicator,Wissant and Cap Blanc-nez,narrative_fallback_3,50.9153407,1.6930064,inferred_text,5000.0,4.57,unknown,reported,raised_beach,narrative fallback: raised beach,"[4.57, 4.57]",null,other,Raised beach evidence at Wissant and Cap Blanc-nez,"Le Petit Blanc Nez, Wissant, Boulogne-sur-Mer, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France métropolitaine, 62179, France",EXPLANATION OF PLATES IV. AND V.,,0.8,Narrative fallback cluster; vertical relation is reported above high-water/highest shingle. Datum is not MSL and should be reviewed. Geocoded from contextual query 'Wissant and Cap Blanc-nez'.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""EXPLANATION OF PLATES IV. AND V."", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""Whilst the appearance of this raised beach and its accompaniments was still fresh in my mind, I chanced to be examining the coast between Wissant and Cap Blanc-nez, when I was much struck by the peculiar appearance of a recent formation, which forms part of a low cliff between the former place and the little hamlet of St. Pol. North of a stream that descends from Sombre-Haute and finds its way through the Sand-dunes to the sea, at about half a mile from Wissant, large blocks of grit, resting upon dark-green sands, and some underlying dark clays, indicate the presence of the Lower Greensand Formation ben""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": 4.57, ""reported_depth_m"": null, ""reported_datum"": ""unknown"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Reported elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""other"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": null, ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",4.57,4.57,4.57,4.57
