bd56ade228aa1e73295a824531469a7efda1173b4a6c05e83707555473073a13,fairbridge1961,sea_level_indicator,Narrative evidence locality,narrative_fallback_1,,,inferred_map,,-24.0,MSL,reported,marine_terrace,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-26.5, -21.5]","""Holocene""",stratigraphic_context,"marine terrace at Narrative evidence locality, reported around 24 m depth",Narrative evidence locality,"forms and raised beaches. A eustatic factor was calculated, that differed with every observer. A new approach is now possible. The p",https://doi.org/10.1016/0079-1946(61)90004-0,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": null, ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""East Indies, parts of the Mediterranean, and the western shores of the Americas. However, it is possible in these regions to use local knowledge in selecting non-active sectors that may be useful. Clearly, if the older terraces are still horizontal over long distances, the younger ones cannot have been warped. In some cases it is noted that the younger, horizontal terraces truncate the undulating pattern of the older (see NAKANO, 1954). Yet another factor of instability can be seen in the great deltas, where compaction of water-saturated muds must inevitably play a great role; but how much and when is not yet clear. This form of subsidence is additional to any regional (tectonic) subsidence which also often coincides with deltas. Data from the Mississippi, the Rhine, the Nile, and other g""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 24.0, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""stratigraphic_context"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": ""Holocene"", ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-24,-24,-24,-24
