bef4c623768f0c686f1ee68a71c72fab89d5e55405966af1b9f6dd11f8434001,martinez-martos2016,sea_level_indicator,5.3. Offshore marine terraces,narrative_fallback_4,,,inferred_map,,-0.0,MSL,reported,marine_terrace,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-2.5, 2.5]",null,other,"marine terrace at 5.3. Offshore marine terraces, reported around 0 m depth",5.3. Offshore marine terraces,Buried marine-cut terraces and submerged marine-built terraces: The Carchuna-Calahonda coastal area (southeast Iberian Peninsula),https://doi.org/10.1016/j.geomorph.2016.04.010,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""5.3. Offshore marine terraces"", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""The \u221280 m marine terrace should also be regarded as a marine-built terrace, as it is the surface expression of a sediment bank. However, its stratigraphic position, overlying an erosional surface and capped by the regressive facies of the most recent Carchuna IPW, would be compatible with a transgressive context. Therefore, we postulate that the \u221280 m depositional terrace is a postglacial feature. In attempting to correlate this depositional terrace with the sea-level record, we propose that this sedimentary body could be regarded as an older analogue of the Carchuna IPW. The generation of""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 0.0, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""other"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": null, ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-0,-0,0,0
17737645cb8d9eac2aac7ed393b334ea6a1f4be2f8801b0dfd76a56cb861d8d9,martinez-martos2016,sea_level_indicator,5.4. Age of marine terraces and onshore-offshore relation,narrative_fallback_5,,,inferred_map,,-90.0,MSL,reported,marine_terrace,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-92.5, -87.5]",150.0,stratigraphic_context,"marine terrace at 5.4. Age of marine terraces and onshore-offshore relation, reported around 90 m depth",5.4. Age of marine terraces and onshore-offshore relation,Buried marine-cut terraces and submerged marine-built terraces: The Carchuna-Calahonda coastal area (southeast Iberian Peninsula),https://doi.org/10.1016/j.geomorph.2016.04.010,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""5.4. Age of marine terraces and onshore-offshore relation"", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""An absolute age can be assigned to all the terraces identified (Figs. 12 and 13). A basement marine-cut terrace at 110 m depth (110a) is the oldest and was formed at approximately 150 ka (Fig. 12). This terrace is only detected by gravity data (Figs. 7 and 8). The next recognizable terrace is the one located at 90 m depth and detected buried onshore (Figs. 7 and 8) as well as offshore (Figs. 9 to 11). This terrace formed at 65 ka during a regressive period (Fig. 12). Later on, in the next regressive period, the marine terrace at 100 m depth was formed at 50\u201335 ka. It can be identified offshore (Fig. 11), but there a""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 90.0, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""stratigraphic_context"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": 150.0, ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-90,-90,-90,-90
