18625d15d8f27c15d1eca282e42495a8afe33d6764846f4ae0f154f56dc11a70,dickinson2007,sea_level_indicator,Koror and Babeldaob as part of the engineering investigations for building an interisland bridge,narrative_fallback_1,,,inferred_map,,-23.5,MSL,reported,marine_terrace,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-26.0, -21.0]","""Holocene""",stratigraphic_context,"marine terrace at Koror and Babeldaob as part of the engineering investigations for building an interisland bridge, reported around 23.5 m depth",Koror and Babeldaob as part of the engineering investigations for building an interisland bridge,The Journal of Island and Coastal Archaeology,https://doi.org/10.1080/15564890701623639,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""Available Cores"", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""In 1975, four bore holes were drilled into fringing reefs (\u201cshoreface terraces\u201d) rising to within 0.1 m of modern low-tide level on the flanks of Toagel Channel (Figure 2) between Koror and Babeldaob as part of the engineering investigations for building an interisland bridge. All the bore holes penetrated the full thickness of Holocene limestone resting unconformably, at depths of 21\u201326 m below mean sea level, on varicolored paleosol or colluvium of presumed Pleistocene age that is 3\u20134 m thick above volcanic basement described as fractured basaltic andesite (Easton and Ku 1980). Multiple cores, each 0.46 m (1.5 ft) long, were taken at interv""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 23.5, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""stratigraphic_context"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": ""Holocene"", ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-23.5,-23.5,-23.5,-23.5
