artially infilled. Where the T""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": null, ""reported_datum"": null, ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": 1.0, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": 1.0, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Elevation sampled from SRTM15+V2 at inferred coordinates because source elevation was not reported. Treat this as approximate spatial context, not a surveyed sample elevation.""}","[{""method"": ""other"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": null, ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""No direct age model extracted from page OCR block.""}]",1,1,1,1
bda0e39f3e1144af45d23aa9c7361625137b114a527fdb34f3a2dc51a1a4a73f,forbes2014,sea_level_indicator,central North Shore of Prince Edward Island,mineru_llm_3_1,,,inferred_map,,null,unknown,other,marine_over_terrestrial_contact,llm-extracted candidate,null,"""9""",lowstand coast,Postglacial lowstand coast stood near the outer edge of the mosaic. Flooded-valley estuaries and their former seaward extensions across the inner shelf are visible.,central North Shore of Prince Edward Island,"Forbes et al. 1999b, 2004; Forbes & Manson 2002; Webster et al. 2002",https://doi.org/10.1144/SP388.18,0.52,Depicts coastal topography and bathymetry from airborne topographic LiDAR and multibeam sounding. No contextual geocode result was found.,"{""page"": ""9"", ""figure"": ""Fig. 7"", ""table"": null, ""section"": null, ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""Postglacial lowstand coast (c. 9 ka) stood near the outer edge of the mosaic.""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": null, ""reported_datum"": null, ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""No coordinates available for DEM elevation sampling.""}","[{""method"": ""lowstand coast"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": ""9"", ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""LLM-assisted extraction; raw BP-like numeric ages are normalized to ka.""}]",,,,
4c1945c4159a4fce3f7e3d2e860312a5f63b528e2864ad603faa84b24b036f33,forbes2014,sea_level_indicator,The transgressive unconformity and subsequent erosion and sedimentation,narrative_fallback_1,,,inferred_map,,-20.0,MSL,reported,submerged_beach,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-22.5, -17.5]",null,other,"submerged beach at The transgressive unconformity and subsequent erosion and sedimentation, reported around 20 m depth",The transgressive unconformity and subsequent erosion and sedimentation,Coastal products of marine transgression in cold-temperate and high-latitude coastal-plain settings: Gulf of St Lawrence and Beaufort Sea,https://doi.org/10.1144/SP388.18,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""The transgressive unconformity and subsequent erosion and sedimentation"", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""and inundated-valley estuaries. Wave quarrying of pits in exposed estuarine sediments at depths of 20 m or more confirms the ongoing deepening of the transgressive unconformity as much as 3 km seaward of the present-day shoreline and 6000 years after the shoreline migrated landward past the point of erosion (Figs 12 & 25a). Pit formation of this kind has not been widely described in the literature, but is known from the Atlantic coast of Nova Scotia (Forbes et al. 1991b). There, as in this study, wave quarrying of cohesive sediments is assumed to begin where the TU becomes exposed at the seabed. Although ice scour penetrating through the TU could be a mechanism for initiation, the depth at which these features are currently encountered would seem to eliminate ice as a plausible trigger.""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 20.0, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""other"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": null, ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-20,-20,-20,-20
