503712618358666fb0522497d2e50f1753ed0f56fce6b781a938664a954ff442,barbosa2018,sea_level_indicator,5.1. Sector I: Upper estuary at the limits of the Holocene transgression,narrative_fallback_1,,,inferred_map,,-1.75,MSL,reported,marine_terrace,narrative fallback: submerged geomorphic sea-level feature,"[-4.25, 0.75]","""Holocene""",stratigraphic_context,"marine terrace at 5.1. Sector I: Upper estuary at the limits of the Holocene transgression, reported around 1.75 m depth",5.1. Sector I: Upper estuary at the limits of the Holocene transgression,Late Quaternary infilling of the Assu River embayment and related sea level changes in NE Brazil,https://doi.org/10.1016/j.margeo.2018.07.014,0.55,Narrative fallback cluster from prose description of submerged palaeolandscape; depth uncertainty widened pending human review.,"{""page"": null, ""figure"": null, ""table"": null, ""section"": ""5.1. Sector I: Upper estuary at the limits of the Holocene transgression"", ""quote_or_paraphrase"": ""eholes were drilled (AS6, AS7 and AS18 in Fig. 6) in the mudflat areas, which were partially occupied by inactive salt works. The low-lying (\u22480 m asl) mudflats were bordered by outcrops from the post Barreiras Formation terraces and the Oligocene basalt outcrops. The XRD mineralogical analysis of sediments from borehole AS18 at depths of 0.35 m, 0.80 m and 2.2 m revealed illite dominant composition (up to 60%) with kaolinite (up to 15%), detritic feldspar and biotite. We collected organic matter samples from borehole AS6 at the 150\u2013155 cm interval, which yielded an age of 7210 cal yr BP (Table 2, Fig. 2). The foraminifera data, combined with the clayey/silty and the organic detritus-rich nature of the sediment, indicated a mangrove environment.""}","{""reported_elevation_m"": null, ""reported_depth_m"": 1.75, ""reported_datum"": ""MSL"", ""reported_uncertainty_m"": null}","{""raw_raster_value_m"": null, ""applied_correction_m"": null, ""derived_elevation_m"": null, ""derived_depth_m"": null, ""derivation_notes"": ""Existing elevation preserved; no raster overwrite applied.""}","[{""method"": ""stratigraphic_context"", ""relation"": ""unknown"", ""age_ka"": ""Holocene"", ""uncertainty_ka"": null, ""material"": null, ""notes"": ""Narrative fallback age context; review before analytical use.""}]",-1.75,-1.75,-1.75,-1.75
